The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 January is 169,375 (19,521.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 January, there were 9,733 new confirmed cases (1,121.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 January, there were 12,544 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 22% (2,811 fewer cases).
